-- Brazil Stock Movers: Hypermarcas, MPX Fall; Iochpe-Maxion Jumps
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-01-11T15:32:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/brazil-stock-movers-hypermarcas-mpx-fall-iochpe-maxion-jumps.html
The following companies are having
 unusual  price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:04 p.m. local time. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  index fell less than 0.1 percent to 59,768.01.  Hypermarcas SA (HYPE3)  (HYPE3 BS) plunged 3.6 percent to 10.30
reais. Banco BTG Pactual SA said it doesn’t plan to make a
hostile bid for shares of the retailer, according to a
regulatory filing. The bank earlier offered to buy a 1 billion
reais ($554 million) stake in Hypermarcas, Bloomberg News
reported yesterday.  Iochpe-Maxion SA (MYPK3)  (MYPK3 BS) rose 1 percent to 27.53 reais.
The vehicle-parts maker said in a filing that its Amsted Maxion
Fundicao e Equipamentos Ferroviarios SA unit has orders this
year worth about 276 million reais.  MPX Energia SA (MPXE3)  (MPXE3 BS), the energy company controlled by
billionaire  Eike Batista , slid 6.4 percent to 45.85 reais.  EON
AG (EOAN) ,  Germany ’s biggest utility, will pay 850 million reais for 10
percent of MPX and will create a power-generation joint venture.  To contact the reporter on this story:
